Process management command:
1: bg- to make the process run in background in case we need to run another process
2: fg- to move the process back from bg to foground
3: nhopup- when we close the terminal , running process on that terminal also stoped but using nhopup that process still runs if we check again 
 from new terminal.
4: nice- with the help of nice command we are able to set priority of the process (priority is from -19 to -20 and lowest hve highest priority )

steps to use bg/fg
1: ctrl+z: this stops the current process
2: jobs: with jobs we are able to see stop process
3: bg: this will put the process at bg to run

